Others have simply

00:36:11.634 --> 00:36:12.227
developed their own

00:36:12.355 --> 00:36:13.926
informal mentoring programs

00:36:14.553 --> 00:36:16.442
without virtue of resources

00:36:17.438 --> 00:36:21.888
and often at the expense of their
own personal scholarship.

00:36:22.174 --> 00:36:24.140
So, we are very grateful to them

00:36:24.443 --> 00:36:25.883
for the work that they do

00:36:26.148 --> 00:36:29.501
and I hope that you will enjoy
meeting them

00:36:29.638 --> 00:36:30.641
in your discussion groups

00:36:30.912 --> 00:36:32.678
because they will serve as guides,

00:36:32.879 --> 00:36:34.222
as you think about the questions

00:36:34.383 --> 00:36:36.541
that we have posed for
these discussion groups.

00:36:37.026 --> 00:36:38.487
So, on behalf of the university,

00:36:38.641 --> 00:36:42.966
we thank you for your
profound contributions to mentoring

00:36:43.426 --> 00:36:46.530
and hope that we can gain insights

00:36:46.858 --> 00:36:50.740
and guidance from you
in the years ahead,

00:36:50.949 --> 00:36:52.796
as we think about mentoring
in the academy.

00:36:53.179 --> 00:36:56.224
Letís give them
a warm round of applause.

00:37:03.781 --> 00:37:05.866
So, we keep on having to
cut off the conversation,

