with some concrete ideas

00:37:18.510 --> 00:37:20.621
about things that we might
be able to try

00:37:20.757 --> 00:37:21.818
in our own environments

00:37:21.903 --> 00:37:22.476
and in some cases

00:37:22.883 --> 00:37:24.979
some very challenging
problems to address.

00:37:25.557 --> 00:37:27.811
I have the pleasure now

00:37:27.811 --> 00:37:30.937
of introducing our Provost,
Steve Hyman

00:37:31.673 --> 00:37:33.441
who is going to share with you

00:37:33.583 --> 00:37:35.771
some University perspectives
on mentoring.

00:37:36.104 --> 00:37:38.328
So, please join me in
welcoming, Steve.

00:37:38.640 --> 00:37:39.640
Thank you.

00:37:44.831 --> 00:37:47.373
Let me start by
thanking you,

00:37:48.581 --> 00:37:50.692
Judy and Lisa

